Haha, yes, I suppose that would be nice if I also posted the answer. Sorry, I'm a dork. <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><br /><br />Kevtris said:<br /><br />1) Multiply all LUT values by 65535 and round down<br />2) Invert the MSbit of the final 16-bit _summed_ result (i.e. pulse_out + tnd_out) to convert the sample to signed.<br />3) Done!<br /><br />And, obviously, if the DAC expects unsigned samples then skip step 2.<br /><br />And thank you for your help tepples! You led me in the right direction!<br /><br /><strong>EDIT: Just FYI, the above solution worked perfectly for me.</strong><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3962">jwdonal</a> — Thu Jun 16, 2011 8:04 pm</p><hr />
