<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7870&amp;p=79954#p79954"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Question on APU Mixer]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7870&amp;p=79954#p79954"><![CDATA[
Floating-point samples generally cover a range from -1.00 to 1.00. Integer samples cover a range from -32768 to 32767. So to convert floating-point samples to integer samples, first clip them to the range [-1.00, 1.00), and then multiply each sample by 32768.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Thu Jun 16, 2011 6:11 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
